 a relatively tight band between roughly 183.60 and 185.10, with several sessions posting small-bodied candles that indicated neither side was willing to commit aggressively. The breakout came on the 29th of June, when a decisive daily close above 185.00 opened the door to the 185.60\u2013185.90 region. A brief pullback in early July \u2014 where price dipped back towards 183.86 on the 2nd \u2014 was absorbed without any meaningful structural damage, and buyers reasserted themselves through the following fortnight. The more recent sequence from the 13th of July onwards has been notably constructive: a series of higher lows and higher highs culminating in yesterday's close at 186.02 and today's early extension to 186.13. The computed zones reinforce this picture \u2014 the 185.99 prior reaction zone, which has registered four prior touches, has now transitioned from overhead friction into a floor that price has cleared and is holding above.\n\nOn the H1 timeframe, the intraday read is equally tidy. From yesterday's 15:00 open around 185.54, price climbed steadily through the overnight session, accelerating through the 186.00 handle in the early hours of this morning and consolidating in a narrow range between 186.02 and 186.13 across the London session. There is no sign of distribution in the hourly candles \u2014 bodies are small but the sequence of higher lows is intact. The nearest resistance of note sits at the 186.22 prior reaction zone, a level that has attracted three prior reactions and represents the immediate ceiling for any further extension.\n\nThe calendar is empty today, which removes the prospect of data-driven volatility spikes in either direction. That cuts both ways \u2014 without a catalyst to force a breakout through 186.22, price may simply continue to consolidate at current levels. On the other hand, thin news flow in a trending market can sometimes allow momentum to carry price quietly through resistance without the usual contest.\n\nThe bullish read would come under pressure on a decisive hourly close back beneath the 185.99 structure, and would be materially challenged by any sustained move below the 185.83 support zone. A break of 185.25 would represent a more significant structural deterioration and would call the broader recovery narrative into question.\n\nThis is editorial analysis, not financial advice. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.", "sample": false}